snippet.title: BANKS
snippet.description:
Official YouTube channel for Harvest/Good Years recording artist BANKS. 

"Heavily influenced by the folk and soul expressions of Fiona Apple and Miss Lauryn Hill, respectively, Banks' tender instrument wavers somewhere between heavy-laden tones and tight, heady melodies. On tracks like "Fall Over" the range of her vocal disparity is effortlessly displayed, Banks' stylistic versatility mirroring something like the younger, electro-funk incarnation of one Florence Welch. Her newest single "Warm Water", released on the U.K. label Good Years Recordings, is a downtempo, melancholy ballad. Despite its lyrical and musical content, however, the track is able to transcend the intended measure of sadness and reach a level of content and sublimeness, only possible through Banks' unique tonal quality and emotional conviction. Produced by the infamous Totally Enormous Extinct Dinosaurs, "Warm Water" exposes all of the artist's vulnerabilities and puts them on display." - IndieCurrent 5/16/13

snippet.title: Negotiating For Humans
snippet.description:
This not a place to get “legal” advice or even a place to discuss “legal” issues. We started this channel because the way people typically do transformational deals is broken and there’s too much value being lost to miserable deal teams to ignore it.

Our experience (and quite a bit of research) tells us that a big part of this is the way deal teams approach this work even before an RFx goes out. Traditional negotiations, deal processes, and contracting processes tend to test attributes that don’t drive success. It’s the intangibles that often make the difference in transformational work.

snippet.title: Haywyre
snippet.description:
Management & Bookings: mgmt@haywyremusic.com

Haywyre is a project that synthesizes the best of two musical genres, that of contemporary electronic, along with the more established traditions of classical and jazz. It has been building and maintaining momentum since its creator, Martin Vogt, returned to the U.S. from Austria in 2008.

Vogt’s primary tool for composition is piano improvisation; it provides the foundation for his work and the core of his musical identity. Having spent endless hours in the studio — and upwards of fourteen years studying piano performance — Martin has honed his craft into the professional sound it is known for today, characterized by exciting, progressive tracks which are crafted with unique composition and seamless design.

snippet.title: Josh Turner Guitar
snippet.description:
Hey! I'm Josh, and I've been posting videos on youtube since I was 15, and since then, the channel has taken me all over the world. Over the years I've gotten to collaborate with dozens of friends who play music, and I've worked with musicians who have since become friends. This channel is about the spirit of collaboration, and keeping an open mind to sounds and ideas both old and new. 

I've published a lot of covers over the years, but I have also released quite a bit of original music, either solo (as Joshua Lee Turner) or with bands such as The Other Favorites and Kingdom Jasmine. 

If you like Rock, Folk, Jazz, Classical, Early Music, R&B, Pop, Bluegrass, Indie, Blues, or pretty much any other genre, then I think you'll find something here for you. 

I'm currently based in Brooklyn, NY, and am touring the world when there isn't a pandemic afoot.

snippet.title: Yvan Jacques

About my channel: 
          (français plus bas)
My movies are spontaneous interpretations of well-known songs, mostly jazz standards. I play both guitar & piano but not in the same time LOL ! 
The song selection and the spontaneous approach reflect my perspective towards playing live night after night, just as I did for a living for about 40 years.

Mes vidéos sont fait spontanément il n'y a pas d'arrangement travaillés pendant des heures,  je joue la pièce avec des moments heureux et d'autres moins. Noté : je joue la guitare et le piano mais pas en même temps LOL

J'ai prévilégiés une approche de musiciens de carrière qui doit jouer les morceaux avec des musiciens différents et dans toutes circonstances. 

Une certaine lecture musical est nécessaire mais pas toujours si  il y a un instrument qui joue la mélodie une bonne connaissance des symboles d'accord s'impose mais surtout l'improvisation est primordial.

snippet.title: Walk That Bass
snippet.description:
Walk That Bass is all about Jazz and Blues. Jazz is a broad and complex genre of music which can be challenging to grasp. It's difficult to even know where to start. This is where this YouTube channel steps in. It offers free Jazz Piano Tutorials that cover everything you need to play the Blues and Jazz. 

My goal in creating this website is to help those who are interested in learning to play and appreciate Jazz. It tries to combine both practical and theoretical aspects, so that you will be able to play Jazz, but also understand why the the thing you are playing sounds good (or bad). 

These Jazz tutorials cover everything from Jazz chords, improvisation, Jazz scales, chord substitution, reharmonization, chord voicings, comping and everything else you need to become a competent and professional sounding Jazz musician.

And if you like my lessons, then check out my website where I upload all my content in writing for your perusal.
http://www.thejazzpianosite.com/
